Crust:25 Oreo chocolate biscuits80g (80ml) butter40g ground almondsBerry coulis:60ml ( cup) water500ml (2 cups) frozen summer berries130ml ( cup) caster sugarJuice of 1 lemon No ordinary cheesecake: 3 unbelievably good bakesFilling:750g full-fat cream cheese, at room temperature200ml double-cream plain yoghurt, at room temperature185ml (4/5 cup) caster sugar5ml (1 tsp) pure vanilla extract2 extra-large eggsDecoration:Baby figs and fresh blueberriesGold dust, optionalMethod:1) Grease a 22cm springform pan. Add a silicone mat on the bottom, topped with greaseproof baking paper.2) For the crust, process the biscuits, butter and almonds until smooth. Press firmly into the base of the pan. Bake at 180 C for 8 minutes. Set aside to cool.3) For the berry coulis, combine the water, berries, sugar and lemon juice and bring to the boil. Simmer until thickened and set aside to cool.4) For the filling, mix the cream cheese, yoghurt, sugar, vanilla and eggs in a processor until smooth.5) Pour the filling over the crust and spoon the berry coulis on top. Use a knife to swirl the coulis through the cheese mixture.6) Bake for 15 minutes at 160 C and a further 45 to 60 minutes at 140 C. Allow to cool in the oven for 1 hour. Then chill overnight in the fridge.